---
import StarlightPage from "@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro";
---

<StarlightPage
  frontmatter={{
    title: "Notes",
    description: "Longer writing on Warden's product and architecture decisions.",
  }}
>
  <section class="notes-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Field notes</p>
    <h2>Longer arguments, outside the landing page.</h2>
    <p>
      The homepage has one job: explain why Warden deserves a look. Notes are where the underlying
      bets can be argued in plain English: why local-first matters, why citations are the product,
      and why the public site stays static until the review engine earns a larger surface.
    </p>

    <div class="note-list">
      <a href="/notes/reviewer-with-receipts/">
        <span>First draft</span>
        <strong>The reviewer should bring receipts</strong>
        <p>
          Why Warden treats the model as a writer, not a witness, and why every confident review
          comment should be able to point at evidence.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</StarlightPage>
